# @PROJECT_NAME@

Generated TI mmWave CMake/Ninja firmware project.

This project references the TI SDK demo at:

```text
@SDK_DEMO_REL@
```

The TI SDK, compilers, and generated firmware are not vendored here.

## Native Build

```bash
cmake -S . -B build -G Ninja -DTI_ROOT=/home/kj/ti
cmake --build build --target firmware
```

## Docker Build From Tool Repository

From the `ti-mmwave-build-tools` repository:

```bash
make project-docker PROJECT=@PROJECT_PATH@
```

Output binary:

```text
build/@PROJECT_NAME@_sdk_demo/@OUTPUT_BIN@
```

## Next Customization Points

- Keep this project as a reference-demo wrapper while validating the board.
- Add local source overlays only after the reference demo is reproducible.
- Keep generated build output under `build/`; do not commit TI SDK source.
